__e: Well, my dear, if Jane should die of this fever, it will be comfort to know that it was all in pursuit of Mr Bingley and under your orders.
Doctors say I'll be on my feet soon.
I'll tell you. If you haven't caught the fever, then there's something unusual in the wind.
If we don't bring it down fast--
And if it ain't essential, you gotta lie in your bunk, hoping that your fever don't get too high, or you gotta find a friend who can afford Tylenol from commissary.
It was touch and go for a while, but your fever broke today.
